Seeded AnalyticsInstance row covers the
published API-first surface only; controller,
service-manager, and registration rollout remain
disabled until the controller-backed promotion
story binds formalSpec.
The provisional lifecycle mapping treats
CREATING as provisioning, ACTIVE as success,
UPDATING as updating, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED, INACTIVE, and DELETED stay
explicit runtime states for the later
controller-backed audit to classify.
Create and delete responses expose work-request
headers while the pinned provider implementation
waits on GetWorkRequest; later runtime stories
must decide whether that remains a lifecycle
contract with breadcrumbs or becomes an explicit
work-request adapter.
PrivateAccessChannel, VanityUrl, and
WorkRequest* stay out of the initial published
surface even though the SDK and provider expose
those auxiliary families.
